docs.text: the most surreal situations are ordinary everyday life as viewed by an outsider .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when those observers are joel and ethan coen , the surreal becomes bizarre .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when the life is that of jeff " the dude " leboswki , the bizarre falls over the edge into the world of " what'sgoingonaroundhere " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the marvelous sound of " the stranger " ( sam elliot ) 's voice-over introduces the film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: at least it does until he forgets what he was going to say and gives up .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the dude ( jeff bridges ) is described as the " laziest man in los angeles , possibly the world " , although he's not so much slothful as he is relaxed .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: spending the last 30 years with a roach clip in one hand and a white russian in the other , he doesn't have much of a life , but he's having a good time .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when asked what he does for fun , he responds " bowl , drive around and the occasional acid flashback " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lebowski's passion is bowling .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when he's not rolling the ball down an alley towards a strike , things just happen to him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: arriving home one night , he's beaten by thugs attempting to collect money that his wife owes them .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even worse , they urinate on his rug .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the problem is that the dude doesn't have a wife .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his assailants realize that their target is a different lebowski when they glance around at his apartment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the " big " lebowski ( david huddleston ) is a multi-millionaire and his dudeness lives in two-room squalor .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the next day , our ragtag hero visits his namesake's mansion attempting compensation for his soaked rug .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the carpet is important to him because it pulls the room together : not surprisingly since it's virtually the only object there .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when he's denied any money , he picks up a replacement rug off the floor .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on his way out , he runs into lebowski's trophy babe wife bunny ( tara reid ) who offers to perform a sexual act that , according to rumor , is one of bill clinton's favorites for a thousand bucks .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the penniless dude wisecracks that he's heading for the cash machine .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: later he gets an unexpected phone call enlisting his aid in being the bag man to deliver a ransom to bunny's kidnappers .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this begins the trademarked coen brothers crimes-gone-wrong sequences .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the kidnappers are impossibly inept .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the dude and his cronies are even worse .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: every plan goes awry .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: you can almost see lebowski's brain churning in slow motion as he tries to figure out the clues .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: that's the story , but to tell the truth it doesn't much matter .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there could be almost any plot and the film would be just as entertaining .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the narrative only exists so we can watch the offbeat characters and the quirky predicaments they fall into .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the dude's bowling buddies walter ( john goodman ) and donny ( steve buscemi ) look like people you'd see on the street but , like everything else in this film , they're not quite what they seem .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: walter is a vet as stuck in vietnam as the dude is in the sixties .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: everything that happens reminds him of a situation in the nam .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when a fellow bowler crosses the foul line but won't admit it , walter pulls a gun on him until he marks a zero on the score sheet .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: donny gets precious few words in between walter's screaming and the dude's rambling .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when he does , walter shouts him down with horrendous albeit seemingly unintentional bowling puns .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: donny is " out of his league " and doesn't " have a frame of reference " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the film is peppered with people for whom the term " character " would be an understatement .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the big lebowski's daughter maude , an avant-garde " vaginal " artist , paints while swinging naked in a leather apparatus like an s&m mary martin .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the kidnappers are german techno nihilist bikers .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: bunny lebowski is a high school cheerleader turned porno star .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: most impressive is john turturro in his far too small role as a hispanic bowler .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as the flamenco music swells , we see him putting on his lavender hose .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the camera pans up to an all-purple skin-tight bowling outfit with " jesus " ( pronounced with a " j " , not an " h " ) embroidered on the pocket .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he addresses the lane with intense seriousness and one painted fingernail .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his tongue slowly snakes out and lovingly licks the glowing bowling ball .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: bridges works the dude as if he had been living him for decades and maybe he has .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i can't think of anyone else who could have done a better job .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: buscemi has a limited role , but he plays it perfectly .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the more that i see john goodman the more convinced i am that he's one of the treasures of our time .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's odd to think that most of the world knows him only as roseanne barr's television husband .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: more like the coen's " raising arizona " than their hit " fargo " , " the big lebowski " demands an open mind and even more open eyes .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a mark of the coen brothers is that even with all wonderful dream sequences and the broad slapstick physical comedy on the screen , much of the humor is subtle and easy to miss .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there's so much going on that frequently it disappears before you can see it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: walking out of the theater , i felt that the film had something important to say .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on further examination , i wasn't sure exactly what it was .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " if you meet jesus at the bowling alley , it's not going to be what you expect " ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " when the going gets weird , the weird go bowling " ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: maybe there's no real message .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: perhaps it's just a roller coaster ride through a hilarious world .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: maybe that's enough .
docs.label: positive
